content: Fun app but needs updating donut won't crash.

Nice idea, but the app keeps crashing after I work on an image for 10 minutes , and I lose everything. Also you need to pay for every single picture to take the tag off the photo, which to me is ridiculous. Apparently there is another version that you dont have to pay for the tag off, but I dont have an iPhone so I cant get it Looked at past reviews who say similar things, and it seems the developer is always promising that these bugs will be fixed.. But they're not.

I love the concept dislike the buggy features and fact that it doesn't save my purchases which is annoying? . I love the artwork but it would be nice if you work out the bugs so I can save my work without it crashing :/. Otherwise I love it is there an option on the Android version to get the full version, together?
Cool little pics to use
I am obsessed with this app!
Paid to use and can't even get into it, it just refuses. Worked for a little while but then things stopped loading and now nothing at all!! NOTHING loads! what a waste of money!

Awesome App Love this and it does work perfectly fine on my Samsung Galaxy Tab S4. I am able to import photographs from my tablet at 13mp and photographs taken with Canon 70D at 20.2mp - both work in this app. The effects are gorgeous! I paid to unlock and remove watermark - well worth the money. The developer is fabulous! Go check out the page on Instagram to see the beautiful creations made using this app.
Lovely effects but my photos don't save good quality
Worked beautifully for about a week and now crashes every single time I open it. I paid for the app and it's the only app on my phone that doesn't work. Very disappointed.

content: Why iap if its paid??
replyContent: Hi!  We launched on iOS 3 years ago and had many people request an Android version of Rainbow Love App.  We are offering promotions for Android as we launch, but we are keeping the app pricing in line with what our iOS users pay.  It's just to be fair.   All purchases are one-time only and unlock the feature for unlimited use.

content: Purchased, then noticed that many of the filters were "locked" with no option to "unlock" them... Any help would be appreciated.
replyContent: Hi there!  Go to the filters editor, select from bottom to add to your image. You can preview and edit all 80 of the locked filters. Option to unlock will come up when you select save from the filter preview or filter editor screen.  You can always write me directly thru the app and thank you for downloading! Kate
